deno run --allow-net test_deepStrictEqual.mjs
deno run --allow-net test_partialDeepStrictEqual.mjs  
deno run --allow-net test_writeEarlyHints.mjs

# Or create a comprehensive test file
deno run --allow-net comprehensive_test.mjs
```

## Implementation Details

### partialDeepStrictEqual Logic
The `partialDeepStrictEqual` function checks if the `expected` value is a subset of the `actual` value:
- For arrays: all elements in `expected` must exist in `actual`
- For objects: all properties in `expected` must exist in `actual` with same values
- For primitives: uses strict equality via `isDeepStrictEqual`

### writeEarlyHints Implementation
The `writeEarlyHints` method:
- Validates that headers haven't been sent yet
- Validates the hints parameter is an object
- Executes the callback asynchronously via `nextTick` to simulate HTTP 103 Early Hints behavior
- Returns `this` for method chaining

### deepStrictEqual Enhancement
Enhanced to properly handle boxed primitives (Number, String, Boolean objects) by ensuring the comparison logic correctly identifies and compares their primitive values.

## Compatibility
These changes maintain full backward compatibility while adding the missing Node.js functionality. All existing code will continue to work as expected.

